SARS-CoV-2 an gano sabon nau'in beta-CoV wanda aka gano 99.98% na gano kwayoyin halitta a cikin samfuran 10 da aka ɗauka daga asalin barkewar cutar, Hunan Seafood Market a Huan.
SARS-CoV-2 ya fi kama da MERS-CoV fiye da SARS-CoV.
Ta hanyar nazarin ƙananan ƙananan lantarki, an gano ƙwayoyin SARS-CoV-2 a cikin ƙananan ƙananan ƙwayoyin cuta na mutum.
An gano ACE2 na ɗan adam a matsayin mai karɓar SARS-CoV-2 da SARS-CoV.
Koyaya, sunadaran S na SARS-CoV-2 suna ɗaure da ACE2 na ɗan adam cikin rauni fiye da sunadaran S na SARS-CoV, wanda hakan ya haifar da rashin kamuwa da cuta mai tsanani ta SARS-CoV-2 fiye da SARS-CoV.
SARS-CoV-2 na iya samar da sabbin ƙananan furotin, waɗanda aka ɓoye ta hanyar orf3b, da furotin mai ɓoyewa wanda aka ɓoye ta hanyar orf8.
SARS-CoV-2 orf3b na iya taka rawa a cikin cututtukan cututtukan cututtuka da hana bayyanar IFNß; duk da haka, orf8 ba ya haɗa da wani yanki ko maƙasudin aiki da aka sani.
A ranar 18 ga Fabrairun 2020, Zhou, et al. sun ba da rahoton cewa cikakken tsarin cryo-EM na ɗan adam ACE2 a ƙudurin 2.9 Å ya haɗu da mai ɗaukar amino acid B0AT1.
Sun gano cewa tsarin kwayar cutar da ke buɗe da rufewa ya haɗu a matsayin dimer kuma ACE2-B0AT1 mai haɗuwa na iya ɗaure sunadarai biyu na S, wanda ke ba da tabbaci na gano CoV da kamuwa da cuta.
B0AT1 na iya zama maƙasudin magani don gwajin magani don shawo kan kamuwa da SARS-CoV-2.
