SARS-CoV-2 yana da kusan kashi 96.2% na nucleotide homology tare da bat COVID RATG13 wanda aka ware daga bat bat da ke da alaƙa da rhinolophus.
Kamar yadda yake a cikin shari'ar SARS-CoV da MERS-CoV, bambancin tsari tsakanin SARS-CoV-2 da RATG13 yana da kyau wajen tantance alaƙar iyaye.
Wannan yana nufin cewa ba za a iya ɗaukar bat a matsayin mai ba da abinci mai guba na SARS-CoV-2 ba, sai dai idan an gano irin wannan cutar ta bat a nan gaba.
Yawancin lokaci, mai ɗaukar hoto na SARS-CoV-2 ya kasance daga nau'in namun daji wanda aka sayar kuma aka kashe a kasuwar sayar da kayan abincin teku ta Hunan, wanda ya haɗa da yawancin shari'o'in farko da suka shafi COVID-19, waɗanda ke nuna yiwuwar yiwuwar yaduwar kwayar cutar ta dabba zuwa mutum.
Yawancin binciken da aka yi kwanan nan, wanda ya danganci jerin abubuwan metagenomic, ya nuna cewa rukunin ƙananan dabbobi masu shayarwa masu haɗari da aka sani da pangolins (manis javanensis - cat eaten) na iya zama tushen asalin beta-CVO da ke da alaƙa da SARS-CoV-2.
Waɗannan sabbin kwayoyin halittar Cov na Pangolins suna da kashi 85-92% na jerin nucleotide tare da SARS-CoV-2.
Duk da haka, suna da alaƙa da RATG13 a kusan kusan 90% daidai a matakin jerin nucleotide.
